{"TopicId":146543,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"Equations for navigating in space","CreatedByName":"KAL 9000","CreatedById":140704,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T20:31:31Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"KAL 9000","CreatedById":140704,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T20:31:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI know the rocket equation and Newton\u0027s gravity equation, but what other equations do you want to have for navigating in the solar system?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bill Phil","CreatedById":127797,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T20:39:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nVis viva equation. Equation of the various conics. The orbital energy equation.There\u0027s a few more out there...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Plusck","CreatedById":153264,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T22:39:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is a most excellent website that provides all of the nuts and bolts:\u00A0 \u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.braeunig.us/space/index.htm\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://www.braeunig.us/space/index.htm\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nedit: oops, that\u0027s the index page for the site. Actual page with equations is \u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.braeunig.us/space/orbmech.htm\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://www.braeunig.us/space/orbmech.htm\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"YNM","CreatedById":98447,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T23:35:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDon\u0027t forget angular momentum - else you don\u0027t know where you are in orbit, eccentricity. Also, many of the \u0022less common\u0022 \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Delta-V\u0022\u003EdV\u003C/abbr\u003E (inclination change, plane change etc.) relies on the different angular momentum.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bill Phil","CreatedById":127797,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T23:52:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSome trig for plane changes.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe keplerian elements.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"GoSlash27","CreatedById":111526,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-26T00:42:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nVector addition for transfer burns crossing \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESoI\u003C/abbr\u003E boundaries.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Delta-V\u0022\u003EDV\u003C/abbr\u003E= sqrt(Vxs^2\u002BVesc^2)-Vorb\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI use this one constantly for mission planning.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nVxs is the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Delta-V\u0022\u003EDV\u003C/abbr\u003E required to set up an intercept, neglecting the current gravity well.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nVesc is the escape velocity from the current gravity well... which happens to be your orbital velocity times sqrt(2).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nVorb is your orbital velocity in the current gravity well.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis can be concatenated (chained) to calculate transfers from a moon about one planet to a moon about a completely different planet.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, gate orbits.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nr=2GM/Vxs^2\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHandy for figuring out the optimal transfer altitudes (not always \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Low Kerbin Orbit\u0022\u003ELKO\u003C/abbr\u003E).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBest,\u003Cbr\u003E\n-Slashy\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"OhioBob","CreatedById":128005,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-26T02:08:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\u0022\u003EI believe there are three equations that form the bedrock of almost all the calculations we do around here.\u00A0 All\u00A0have already been mentioned in some form or another, but I\u0027ll summarize.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\u0022\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tsiolkovsky_rocket_equation\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003ETsiolkovsky rocket equation\u003C/a\u003E,\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022margin:0in 0in 8pt;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\u0022\u003E\u003Cfont color=\u0022#000000\u0022\u003E\u0394v = v\u003C/font\u003E\u003Csub\u003E\u003Cfont color=\u0022#000000\u0022\u003Ee\u003C/font\u003E\u003C/sub\u003E\u003Cfont color=\u0022#000000\u0022\u003E LN(m\u003C/font\u003E\u003Csub\u003E\u003Cfont color=\u0022#000000\u0022\u003Eo\u003C/font\u003E\u003C/sub\u003E\u003Cfont color=\u0022#000000\u0022\u003E / m\u003C/font\u003E\u003Csub\u003E\u003Cfont color=\u0022#000000\u0022\u003Ef\u003C/font\u003E\u003C/sub\u003E\u003Cfont color=\u0022#000000\u0022\u003E)\u003C/font\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\u0022\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vis-viva_equation\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EVis-viva equation\u003C/a\u003E,\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\u0022\u003Ev\u003Csup\u003E2\u003C/sup\u003E = GM (2/r - 1/a)\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\u0022\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.braeunig.us/space/orbmech.htm#HEV\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EHyperbolic excess velocity\u003C/a\u003E,\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022margin:0in 0in 8pt;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\u0022\u003E\u003Cfont color=\u0022#000000\u0022\u003Ev\u003C/font\u003E\u003Csub\u003E\u003Cfont color=\u0022#000000\u0022\u003E\u221E\u003C/font\u003E\u003C/sub\u003E\u003Csup\u003E\u003Cfont color=\u0022#000000\u0022\u003E2\u003C/font\u003E\u003C/sup\u003E\u003Cfont color=\u0022#000000\u0022\u003E = v\u003C/font\u003E\u003Csub\u003E\u003Cfont color=\u0022#000000\u0022\u003Ebo\u003C/font\u003E\u003C/sub\u003E\u003Csup\u003E\u003Cfont color=\u0022#000000\u0022\u003E2\u003C/font\u003E\u003C/sup\u003E\u003Cfont color=\u0022#000000\u0022\u003E \u2013 v\u003C/font\u003E\u003Csub\u003E\u003Cfont color=\u0022#000000\u0022\u003Eesc\u003C/font\u003E\u003C/sub\u003E\u003Csup\u003E\u003Cfont color=\u0022#000000\u0022\u003E2\u003C/font\u003E\u003C/sup\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022margin:0in 0in 8pt;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cfont face=\u0022Verdana\u0022\u003EMaster those three equations and you\u0027ll be in good shape.\u003C/font\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}